fields.description:
This is the same issue as https://bitbucket.org/site/master/issue/8320/pull-requests-to-a-closed-branch-cannot-be - it appears to have reverted recently.

{code}
The following error(s) occurred saving this pull request

Can&#x27;t create branch [branch-name] since it already exists in [repository-name].
{code}

I can&#x27;t have access to my account repo. I tried using:

ssh -T git@bitbucket.org

then:

{code}
#!shell
authenticated via a deploy key.


You can use git or hg to connect to Bitbucket. Shell access is disabled.

This deploy key has read access to the following repositories:

oswferreira/manutencao-industrial:  -- osw@bloodstone.local
oswferreira/grupopontes: macbook -- osw@bloodstone.local
{code}

I&#x27;ve deleted all deployment-keys and regenerated ssh-keys (adding the new ones) and still can&#x27;t access the repo.

{code}
#!shell

onq: repository access denied. deployment key is not associated with the requested repository.
fatal: Could not read from remote repository.
{code}

The command

{code}
git clone git@bitbucket.org:iverticledevteam/iverticle_playbooks.git
{code}

Produces the following error:

{code}
Cloning into &#x27;iverticle_playbooks&#x27;...
conq: repository does not exist.
fatal: The remote end hung up unexpectedly
{code}

I know the repository exists, and I can check it out just fine using https. I am also certain that the deploy key I am using works properly.
